public interface Proxiable

Proxiability of a class is enabled by the class implementing the org.ink.core.vm.proxy.Proxiable interface. Classes that do not implement this interface will not have their state proxied. All subtypes of a proxiable class are themselves proxiable. The Proxiable interface declares a predicate named isProxied, which returns a boolean value.
